description:
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Royal Brompton and Harefield NHS Foundation Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Royal Brompton Hospital &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Consultant &lt;strong&gt;in &lt;strong&gt;Cardiovascular Magnetic Resonance&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reference: 312-RBH-CON-CARD-0004&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Royal Brompton &amp; Harefield NHS Foundation Trust is seeking to appoint a Consultant in Cardiovascular Magnetic Resonance at the Royal Brompton Hospital also linked to St Thomas’ Hospital. This is a replacement post; it is a whole-time Consultant in Cardiovascular Magnetic Resonance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for the post of Consultant in Cardiovascular Magnetic Resonance to join a successful and enthusiastic team delivering the clinical CMR service. The post-holder will have up to 4 sessions working in the clinical service at St Thomas’s Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will participate in the running of the Clinical CMR service scans at consultant level. More particularly Supervise CMR scanning and advise fellows and technologists, CMR reporting with final sign-off of clinical reports. The post holder will be involved with the management, teaching, mentoring and supervision of clinical CMR fellows.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will participate and contribute to cross-site Trust MDT’s; also, to develop, participate and contribute to inter-institutional MDT’s.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will undertake lectures and the training of colleagues.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants are required to be fully registered Medical Practitioners and must be on the GMC’s Specialist Register or be eligible for admission to the Register within six months from date of interview for the post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal enquiries may be made to Professor Dudley Pennell, Cross-site Director of Heart Assessment on 0207 351 8800 (dj.pennell@rbht.nhs.uk). Alternatively, please contact the Medical Recruitment team, Sophia White on 0207 351 8688 (s.white3@bht.nhs.uk).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please apply for the position using the &quot;Apply for this job&quot; button. Please complete the online application form and include the full names, work addresses and fax numbers of three clinical referees, one of which must be your current or most recent employer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Shortlisting details and interview arrangements will be communicated via email therefore please ensure you check your email account regularly following the closing date. In addition the Trust will be chasing up references via email so please ensure you include the email addresses and contact numbers for your referees to avoid delay in the recruitment process.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date: Friday 13th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview date: Friday 11th December 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
